; Regression test for issue #696: Change to -F parsing rules (casting to int) (BZ#696)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/696
;
; The bug: adding an integer literal to total_width fails with
; "Cannot add a string to an amount" when the literal is on the left.
; `4 + total_width` fails, but `total_width + 4` works.
; Workaround: use int(total_width) to explicitly cast to integer.

2024/01/01 Test
    Expenses:Food    $10.00
    Assets:Cash

test reg -F "%(justify(scrub(display_total), 4 + total_width, true, color))\n" -> 1
__ERROR__
While evaluating value expression:
  justify(scrub(display_total), (4 + total_width), true, color)
While adding 12 to 4:
While calling function 'justify ($10.00, <#EXPR ({4} + total_width)>, <#EXPR true>, 0)':
While handling posting from "$FILE", line 10:
>     Expenses:Food    $10.00
Error: Cannot add a string to an amount
end test
